  "prompt": "I want to read about Swami Vivekananda. Tell me one or two good books on Swami Vivekananda?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are two highly recommended books on Swami Vivekananda:\n\n1. **\"The Complete Works of Swami Vivekananda\"** - This multi-volume set contains all of Swami Vivekananda's writings, lectures, letters, and conversations. It's a comprehensive collection that provides a deep insight into his philosophy, thoughts, and teachings.\n\n2. **\"Swami Vivekananda: A Biography\" by Swami Nikhilananda** - This book is a well-written and accessible biography that covers Swami Vivekananda's life, his journey to the West, his impact on Hindu spirituality, and his lasting legacy.\n\nBoth these books offer valuable insights into the life and teachings of Swami Vivekananda and are great starting points for anyone interested in learning about this influential spiritual leader.",
